2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed framework has wide applicability in various fields such as bioinformatics, chemoinformatics, social network analysis, and data mining, which are all related to AI. 
3. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The proposed framework can be used for graph classification tasks, which are often used in computer vision and pattern recognition. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper mentions social network analysis as one of the fields where the proposed framework can be applied. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper mentions data mining as one of the fields where the proposed framework can be applied, which is related to natural language processing and text mining.
